017package org.apache.juneau.bean.html5;
018
019import org.apache.juneau.annotation.*;
020import org.apache.juneau.internal.*;

022/**
023 * DTO for an HTML <a class="doclink" href="https://www.w3.org/TR/html5/sections.html#the-h1,-h2,-h3,-h4,-h5,-and-h6-elements">&lt;h1&gt;</a>
024 * element.
025 *
026 * <p>
027 * The h1 element represents the highest level heading in a document or section. It is used to
028 * mark up the main title or most important heading on a page. The h1 element should be used
029 * only once per page and should describe the main topic or purpose of the page. It is typically
030 * rendered in the largest font size among all heading elements and is important for both
031 * accessibility and SEO.
032 *
033 * <h5 class='section'>Examples:</h5>
034 * <p class='bcode w800'>
035 *    <jk>import static</jk> org.apache.juneau.bean.html5.HtmlBuilder.*;
036 * 
037 *    <jc>// Simple page title</jc>
038 *    H1 <jv>simple</jv> = <jsm>h1</jsm>(<js>"Welcome to Our Website"</js>);
039 * 
040 *    <jc>// H1 with styling</jc>
041 *    H1 <jv>styled</jv> = <jsm>h1</jsm>(<js>"About Our Company"</js>)
042 *       ._class(<js>"page-title"</js>);
043 * 
044 *    <jc>// H1 with complex content</jc>
045 *    H1 <jv>complex</jv> = <jsm>h1</jsm>(
046 *       <js>"Welcome to "</js>,
047 *       <jsm>strong</jsm>(<js>"Our Company"</js>),
048 *       <js>" - "</js>,
049 *       <jsm>em</jsm>(<js>"Innovation at its finest"</js>)
050 *    );
051 * 
052 *    <jc>// H1 with ID</jc>
053 *    H1 <jv>withId</jv> = <jsm>h1</jsm>(<js>"Product Documentation"</js>)
054 *       .id(<js>"main-title"</js>);
055 * 
056 *    <jc>// H1 with styling</jc>
057 *    H1 <jv>styled2</jv> = <jsm>h1</jsm>(<js>"User Guide"</js>)
058 *       .style(<js>"color: #333; text-align: center; margin-bottom: 30px;"</js>);
059 * 
060 *    <jc>// H1 with multiple elements</jc>
061 *    H1 <jv>multiple</jv> = <jsm>h1</jsm>(
062 *       <js>"Chapter 1: "</js>,
063 *       <jsm>span</jsm>()._class(<js>"chapter-title"</js>).children(<js>"Getting Started"</js>),
064 *       <js>" "</js>,
065 *       <jsm>small</jsm>(<js>"(Beginner Level)"</js>)
066 *    );
067 * 
068 *    <jc>// H1 with links</jc>
069 *    H1 <jv>withLinks</jv> = <jsm>h1</jsm>(
070 *       <js>"Product: "</js>,
071 *       <jsm>a</jsm>(<js>"/products/widget"</js>, <js>"Amazing Widget"</js>),
072 *       <js>" v2.0"</js>
073 *    );
074 * </p>
075 *
076 * <p>
077 * The following convenience methods are provided for constructing instances of this bean:
078 * <ul class='javatree'>
079 *    <li class='jc'>{@link HtmlBuilder}
080 *    <ul class='javatree'>
081 *       <li class='jm'>{@link HtmlBuilder#h1() h1()}
082 *       <li class='jm'>{@link HtmlBuilder#h1(Object, Object...) h1(Object, Object...)}
083 *    </ul>
084 * </ul>
085 * </p>
086 *
087 * <h5 class='section'>See Also:</h5><ul>
088 *    <li class='link'><a class="doclink" href="https://juneau.apache.org/docs/topics/JuneauBeanHtml5">juneau-bean-html5</a>
089 * </ul>
090 */
091@Bean(typeName="h1")
092public class H1 extends HtmlElementMixed {
093
094   /**
095    * Creates an empty {@link H1} element.
096    */
097   public H1() {}
098
099   /**
100    * Creates an {@link H1} element with the specified child nodes.
101    *
102    * @param children The child nodes.
103    */
104   public H1(Object...children) {
105      children(children);
106   }
